---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE, SOCIALS } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout title="About me" description="Who Tuan Nguyen is, what I work on, and how to get in touch.">
  <article class="post">
    <h1 class="post-title">About me</h1>
    <div class="post-content">
      <p>Hi, I'm <strong>Tuan Nguyen</strong>. I write here in two flavours:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Product space</strong> — how I think about products, discovery, and shipping.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical space</strong> — engineering deep-dives and what I learn building software.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <p>
        I'm a software engineer who enjoys turning fuzzy problems into systems
        that are simple to reason about. I care about clean architecture,
        pragmatic trade-offs, and shipping things that actually help the people
        using them.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blog is where I think out loud — half about how products get built
        and why, half about the engineering details that make them work.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a></li>
        {SOCIALS.map((s) => (
          <li>{s.label}: <a href={s.href} rel="me">{s.href.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '')}</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
